&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is:&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Slaughter&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul style=&quot;&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Carnage&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;means the violent killing of a large number of people.

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Example -&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;em&gt;The Battle of Gettysburg was a scene of dreadful &lt;strong&gt;carnage&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Marked option&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Slaughter&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;means to kill a large number of people at one time, especially in a cruel way.
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Example -&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;em&gt;Thousands of people were &lt;strong&gt;slaughtered &lt;/strong&gt;in the civil war.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;It is clear that&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;#39;Carnage&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;and&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;#39;Slaughter&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;are similar in meaning.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Therefore the correct answer is&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;option 2&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul style=&quot;&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Lust&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;means &amp;nbsp;to have a strong desire for something.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Plague&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;means to cause worry, pain, or difficulty to someone or something over a period of time.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Revelry&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;means a situation in which people are drinking, dancing, singing, etc. at a party or in public.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;A quantity too small to make an impact&amp;#39;.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Idiom&lt;strong&gt; &amp;#39;A drop in the ocean&amp;#39; &lt;/strong&gt;means a very small amount which is unimportant compared to the cost of other things or is so small that it has very little effect on something.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;For example:
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;His fee is a &lt;strong&gt;drop in the ocean &lt;/strong&gt;compared with the real cost of broadcasting.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Thus, &lt;strong&gt;option 3&lt;/strong&gt; will be the correct answer.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;An &lt;strong&gt;idiom &lt;/strong&gt;has been used in the sentence.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;An &lt;strong&gt;idiom&lt;/strong&gt; is a phrase or expression that &lt;strong&gt;typically presents a figurative, non literal meaning to the phrase.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Let&amp;#39;s take a look at some common idioms:&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;table border=&quot;1&quot; cellpadding=&quot;2&quot; cellspacing=&quot;2&quot; style=&quot;width: 350px;&quot;&gt;
	&lt;tbody&gt;
		&lt;tr&gt;
			&lt;td&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;Idioms&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
			&lt;td style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;Meanings&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
		&lt;/tr&gt;
		&lt;tr&gt;
			&lt;td&gt;A bird in the hand&lt;/td&gt;
			&lt;td&gt;Used to say that it is better to hold onto something one has than to risk losing it by trying to get something better.&lt;/td&gt;
		&lt;/tr&gt;
		&lt;tr&gt;
			&lt;td&gt;Beat around the bush&lt;/td&gt;
			&lt;td&gt;Avoid saying what you mean, usually because it is uncomfortable.&lt;/td&gt;
		&lt;/tr&gt;
	&lt;/tbody&gt;
&lt;/table&gt;

&lt;p dir=&quot;ltr&quot;&gt;The correct answer is &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;revealed.&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p dir=&quot;ltr&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul dir=&quot;ltr&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li role=&quot;presentation&quot;&gt;Disclose means to make (secret or new information) known. (गुप्त या नई जानकारी का खुलासा करना।)
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li role=&quot;presentation&quot;&gt;Example Sentence: The scientist disclosed his revolutionary new discovery to the world.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li role=&quot;presentation&quot;&gt;Revealed also refers to the act of making previously unknown or secret information known. (अज्ञात या गुप्त जानकारी का खुलासा करना।)
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li role=&quot;presentation&quot;&gt;Example Sentence: She revealed the truth about her past to her family.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p dir=&quot;ltr&quot; role=&quot;presentation&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Therefore, the correct answer is Option 1.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p dir=&quot;ltr&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul dir=&quot;ltr&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li role=&quot;presentation&quot;&gt;Deceived: Mislead or trick someone. (किसी को भ्रमित करना,&amp;nbsp;धोखा देना।)&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li role=&quot;presentation&quot;&gt;Concealed: Kept secret; hidden. (गुप्त रखना; छिपाना।)&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li role=&quot;presentation&quot;&gt;Superseded: Take the place of (a person or thing previously in authority or use); supplant. (बदल देना, प्रतिस्थापित करना।)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is Orchard.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Orchard &lt;/strong&gt;means-&amp;nbsp;A piece of enclosed land planted with fruit trees.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example&lt;/strong&gt;-&amp;nbsp;&lt;em&gt;Her black bicycle is leaning against the orchard fence.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Let us look at the meanings of the other words:&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Nursery&lt;/strong&gt;-&amp;nbsp;a place where young plants are grown and sold (पौधशाला, (जहाँ छोटे पौधे उगाए और बेचे जाते है), नर्सरी)&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Bouquet&lt;/strong&gt;-&amp;nbsp;An arrangement of flowers that is usually given as a present. (आकर्षक रूप से व्यवस्थित फूलों का गुच्छा; गुलदस्&amp;zwj;ता, पुष्&amp;zwj;पगुच्&amp;zwj;छ)&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Flotilla&lt;/strong&gt;-&amp;nbsp;A small fleet of ships or boats. (&lt;span style=&quot;display: none;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;)&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Hence, the most appropriate answer is &lt;strong&gt;option 1.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;Nocturnal&amp;#39;.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Nocturnal&lt;/strong&gt; means &lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;happening or active&amp;nbsp;during the night&amp;quot;.&lt;/strong&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;E.g.&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;most owls are &lt;strong&gt;nocturnal&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;According to the meaning and example that are given above, &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;nocturnal&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39; is the correct answer.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;All other words are wrongly spelt.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is&lt;strong&gt; &amp;#39;Go out on a limb&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&amp;quot;&lt;strong&gt;Go out on a limb&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;quot; is an idiom that means to take a risk or put yourself in a vulnerable position by stating something that may be unpopular or controversial.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The sentence talks about&lt;strong&gt; taking a risk&lt;/strong&gt; to predict something, so the idiom fits the context well.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;This option reflects the sentiment of risking a prediction, consistent with the original phrase.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;It aligns with the courage and risk associated with predicting an uncertain outcome.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;Therefore, the correct answer is Option 4.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&amp;quot;&lt;strong&gt;Turn over a new leaf&amp;quot;&lt;/strong&gt; means to start behaving in a better way.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&amp;quot;&lt;strong&gt;Pull the plug&amp;quot;&lt;/strong&gt; means to stop something.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;Bite the dust&amp;quot;&lt;/strong&gt; means to die or fail.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;Unproductive&amp;#39;.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The word &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;Prolific&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt; means &lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;producing many works, etc.&amp;quot;&lt;/strong&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;E.g.&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;one of the most &lt;strong&gt;prolific&lt;/strong&gt; periods in her career.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The word &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;Unproductive&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt; means &lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;not producing very much; not producing good results&amp;quot;&lt;/strong&gt;.
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;E.g.&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;I&amp;#39;ve had a very &lt;strong&gt;unproductive&lt;/strong&gt; day.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;According to the meanings of the words and the examples given above, &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;unproductive&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39; is the correct antonym of the word &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;prolific&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Let&amp;#39;s know the meanings of other words:&lt;/strong&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Abundant-&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;existing in large quantities; more than enough.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Several-&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;​more than two but not very many.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Rich-&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;containing or providing a large supply of something.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;dispassionate&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The most appropriate &lt;strong&gt;antonym&lt;/strong&gt; of the given word &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;Ardent&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39; is &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;Dispassionate&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Ardent&lt;/strong&gt;:&amp;nbsp;showing strong feelings, especially a strong liking for somebody/something (मजबूत भावनाओं को दिखाना, विशेष रूप से किसी के लिए एक मजबूत पसंद)&amp;nbsp;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;Example:&amp;nbsp;He was an &lt;strong&gt;ardent&lt;/strong&gt; supporter of Mohun Bagan.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Dispassionate&lt;/strong&gt;:&amp;nbsp;not influenced by strong emotion, and so able to be rational and impartial (मजबूत भावना से प्रभावित नहीं है, और इसलिए तर्कसंगत और निष्पक्ष होने में सक्षम है)
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;Example: She&amp;nbsp;dealt with life&amp;#39;s disasters in a calm, &lt;strong&gt;dispassionate&lt;/strong&gt; way.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
		&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;Correct Answer:&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;em&gt;dispassionate.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Let&amp;#39;s look at the meaning of other words:
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;emotional&lt;/strong&gt;:&amp;nbsp;connected with people&amp;rsquo;s feelings (लोगों की भावनाओं से जुड़ा)&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;encouraging&lt;/strong&gt;:&amp;nbsp;giving someone support or confidence; supportive (किसी को समर्थन या विश्वास देना; सहायक)&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;humble&lt;/strong&gt;: having or showing a modest or low estimate of one&amp;#39;s importance (किसी के महत्व का मामूली या कम अनुमान होना या दिखाना)&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
